  "texts": [
    "Thus, we have shown that ■ ′ i X ′ = min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ ■ i X, so P ′ is closed under ■ ′ i because P is closed under ■ i.For part 2, every set of minimal points in F satisfies persistence and refinability, so if F is full, then every set of minimal points in F belongs to P and therefore to P ′ by Definition 4.15.3, so AtF is full.For part 3, since ⊑ ′ and R ′ i are the restrictions of ⊑ and R i to S ′, the identity map h on S ′ satisfies the requirements of a strong embedding that a ⊑ ′ b iff h(a) ⊑ h(b), and aR ′ i b iff h(a)R i h(b).",
    "Moreover, since ⊑ ′ is the identity relation, h satisfies ⊑-back and hence ⊑-matching.",
    "It only remains to show:• R-matching -∀a ∈ S ′ ∀X ∈ P: R i (h(a)) ⊆ X iff R ′ i (a) ⊆ h -1 [X]; • pull back -∀X ∈ P: h -1 [X] ∈ P ′; • embedding -∀X ′ ∈ P ′ ∃X ∈ P: h[X ′] = h[S ′] ∩ X; • dense -∀x ∈ S ∃a ∈ S ′: h(a) ⊑ x.For pull back, for anyX ∈ P, h -1 [X] = min⟨S, ⊑⟩∩X ∈ P ′.",
    "For R-matching, since h(a) = a and h -1 [X] = min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ X, we must show that R i (a) ⊆ X iff R ′ i (a) ⊆ min⟨S, ⊑⟩∩X.",
    "This follows from the fact, established in the proof of part 1, that min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ ■ i X = ■ ′ i (min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ X).Finally, from the facts that h is the identity map and S ′ = min⟨S, ⊑⟩, the embedding condition is just that for all X ′ ∈ P ′ there is an X ∈ P such that X ′ = min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ X, which is immediate from the definition of P ′ in Definition 4.15.3."
  ]
}